      <h5 class="link">Public Announcement: Important Notice on Illegal Transportation of Animals</h5>
      <div class="content-div">
         <p class="css-6f2r2t">This is an important public announcement to inform all the Animal Transporters about the provisions related to the transportation of animals by vehicle. Violations of these provisions will result in strict legal action. We urge everyone to comply with the following regulations and obtain the necessary licenses for transporting animals: <span class="bold-text">Special  License Requirement:</span> According to Section 125 (E) of the Central Motor Vehicles Rules, 1989, every vehicle used for transporting animals must obtain a special license from Local Transport Office (RTO).<span class="bold-text">Compliance with Indian Standards:</span> Vehicle owners must ensure that their vehicles meet the standards set by the Indian  Institute, specifically IS-14904:2007, IS-5236:2001, or IS-5236:1982.<span class="bold-text">Adherence to the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960:</span> All transportation of animals must comply with the provisions of the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960, issued by the Central Government. Failure to adhere to the above rules will lead to strict legal action under the Motor Vehicle Rules and the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960. Issued by: <span class="name top-gap">General Manager (Deonar Slaughterhouse)</span><span class="name">Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation</span><span class="name">(As per order)</span></p>
